## 2) Two numbering systems (this prevents confusion)
### A) Architecture Layers (L1–L9) — what CareerOS is
- **L1:** Entry / UX (Streamlit UI, forms, dashboards)
- **L2:** Backend API (FastAPI endpoints + validation)
- **L3:** Orchestration Core (Planner/Director behavior; pipeline now, LangGraph later)
- **L4:** Agent Layer (job understand/match/tailor behaviors; deterministic now, agents later)
- **L5:** Human Approval Gates (approve shortlist/package/sensitive actions)
- **L6:** Execution & Tracking (export + lifecycle ledger + followups)
- **L7:** Analytics & Learning (funnel + metrics + A/B later)
- **L8:** Memory & Models (DB + vector DB + embeddings + LLMs later)
- **L9:** Governance / Explainability / Ops (audit logs, guardrails, CI/CD hooks)

### B) Build Pipeline Steps (P1–P18+...) — how I’m building it
- **Phase 1:** P1–P12 (deterministic spine)
- **Phase 2:** P13–P18 (RAG + LLM grounding + hybrid reasoning)
- **Phase 3:** P19–P24 (real agent orchestration)
- **Phase 4:** P25–P32 (CI/CD, Docker/K8s, monitoring, drift, MLOps)

✅ **Rule:** One P-step can touch multiple L-layers.

